  "playingCareerSummary": "Former Australia captain and one of the greatest Test batters of all time: 168 Tests (13,378 runs), 375 ODIs. 2-time ODI World Cup winning captain. Played for KKR in 2008 and MI in 2013 in the IPL.",
  "bio": "The most-tenured overseas coach in the IPL. Started his head-coaching career at Mumbai Indians (2015-2016), winning the 2015 title in his first season. Moved to Delhi in 2018 (Delhi Daredevils) and continued through the franchise's 2019 rebrand to Delhi Capitals, serving seven seasons and transforming them from serial under-achievers into consistent contenders, reaching the 2020 final (lost to MI) and topping the league in 2021. Parted ways with DC ahead of the 2025 mega auction and was appointed Punjab Kings head coach in September 2024 — his fourth IPL franchise role. Delivered PBKS's second-ever IPL final in 2025 (lost to RCB by 6 runs) in his first season. Retained for 2026.",
